.TH CPY 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cpy \- copy a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cpy
.I source
.I dest
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cpy
copies
.I source
to
.IR dest .
On Linux,
.BR sendfile (2)
is used for efficient kernel-space transfer; on other POSIX systems
a portable
.BR fread (3)
/
.BR fwrite (3)
loop is used as a fallback.
.PP
If
.I dest
exists it is overwritten.
Permissions of the source file are preserved via
.BR fstat (2).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open source or destination.
.TP
.B 3
I/O error during copy.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Copy a file:
.EX
cpy notes.txt notes.bak
.EE
.TP
Copy into a directory path:
.EX
cpy config.conf /etc/myapp/config.conf
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cp (1),
.BR move (1)
